# Rotation Layers
# This is to predict rotation speed. The easiest change would be to modify
# num_output from "fc8-shapes" to 5, then retrain the bounding box and
# rotation parameters together. Instead the rotation output is generated
# through a distinct and parallel set of layers for the following reasons:
# 1) Avoid "change one thing, change everything" for safer experimentation
# 2) Easy loading of existing weights as bbox layers are preserved
# 3) GOTURN paper advises that it takes 50,000 iterations to start seeing
# results from the bbox training (5 hours of training on K80 GPU).
# If layers are combined, then this becomes a minimum on training time
# and would slow development. Additionally if the bbox layers broke or
# were insufficiently trained, then the tracking fails entirely.
# Pre-trained weights are much more reliable by comparison.
#
# The lr_mult and decay_mult values are reused from the bbox layers.
# The bbox layers have learning disabled (lr_mult: 0) so that training
# is only done on the rotation layers.
#
# The rotation layers are named the same as the shapes layers but with a
# "-rot" suffix. This allows reuse of the mental model from the shapes layer
# whilst being clearly distinct. The num_output of 4k, 4k & 1k are likely
# excessive for predicting a single output. The goal is first to get the
# system working and then improve performance. Nonetheless the same
# layout structure and starting parameters are used as the bbox layer
# to make it easier to combine them later.
#
# TODO:
# A) Training might be faster if it trained on only the fc8-rot layer.
# B) Consolidate the layers back together to reduce computational overhead,
# then increase num_outputs of "fc8-shapes" to 5 to output bbox and rotation.
# C) Retrain the fully connected layers to maintain the existing bbox
# accuracy and a sufficient accuracy for rotation.
# D) If if it isn't possible to get the required accuracy, consider increasing
# increasing the size of the fully connected layers to compensate for
# generating the additional rotation output.

layer {
  name: "fc6-new-rot"
  type: "InnerProduct"
  bottom: "pool5_concat"
  top: "fc6-rot"
  param {
    lr_mult: 10
    decay_mult: 1
  }
  param {
    lr_mult: 20
    decay_mult: 0
  }
  inner_product_param {
    num_output: 4096
    weight_filler {
      type: "gaussian"
      std: 0.005
    }
    bias_filler {
      type: "constant"
      value: 1
    }
  }
}
